 is `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns` (0–5, default 5).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:- `all`: any session (cross-agent access still requires `tools.agentToAgent`).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:    agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 5 },\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:### `tools.agentToAgent`\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:- `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md:- `routing.agentToAgent` → `tools.agentToAgent`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":216,"aggregated":"API Key: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\nAuth Token: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/transcript-hygiene.md:agent-to-agent reply/announce steps), OpenClaw persists the created user turn with:\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:- `sessions_send` runs a reply‑back ping‑pong (reply `REPLY_SKIP` to stop; max turns via `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`, 0–5).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/multi-agent.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/concepts/session-tool.md:  - 最大轮数为 `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`（0–5，默认 5）。\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/tools/index.md:- `sessions_send` 运行回复往返乒乓（回复 `REPLY_SKIP` 以停止；最大轮次通过 `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`，0-5）。\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:### `tools.agentToAgent`（可选）\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/configuration.md:- `agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`：请求者/目标之间的最大回复轮次（0–5，默认 5）。\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/zh-CN/gateway/doctor.md:- `routing.agentToAgent` → `tools.agentToAgent`\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:  // Off by default: agent-to-agent messaging must be explicitly enabled + allowlisted.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:  - Max turns is `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns` (0–5, default 5).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md:- `all`: any session (cross-agent access still requires `tools.agentToAgent`).\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:    agentToAgent: { maxPingPongTurns: 5 },\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:### `tools.agentToAgent`\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:    agentToAgent: {\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md:- `all`: any session. Cross-agent targeting still requires `tools.agentToAgent`.\n/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/doctor.md:- `routing.agentToAgent` → `tools.agentToAgent`","cwd":"/home/hochoy/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774011491183}}
{"type":"message","id":"f490ffc2","parentId":"2d6c09af","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:14.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我读取更多关于 agentToAgent 配置的官方文档。","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_V7JJ4SELYegTfyGCbp0fgsdJ","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md","limit":150,"offset":1}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":918,"output":50,"cacheRead":49664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50632,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774011491186}}
{"type":"message","id":"230525cf","parentId":"f490ffc2","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:14.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_V7JJ4SELYegTfyGCbp0fgsdJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntitle: \"Configuration Reference\"\ndescription: \"Complete field-by-field reference for ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"\nsummary: \"Complete reference for every OpenClaw config key, defaults, and channel settings\"\nread_when:\n  - You need exact field-level config semantics or defaults\n  - You are validating channel, model, gateway, or tool config blocks\n---\n\n# Configuration Reference\n\nEvery field available in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`. For a task-oriented overview, see [Configuration](/gateway/configuration).\n\nConfig format is **JSON5** (comments + trailing commas allowed). All fields are optional — OpenClaw uses safe defaults when omitted.\n\n---\n\n## Channels\n\nEach channel starts automatically when its config section exists (unless `enabled: false`).\n\n### DM and group access\n\nAll channels support DM policies and group policies:\n\n| DM policy           | Behavior                                                        |\n| ------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `pairing` (default) | Unknown senders get a one-time pairing code; owner must approve |\n| `allowlist`         | Only senders in `allowFrom` (or paired allow store)             |\n| `open`              | Allow all inbound DMs (requires `allowFrom: [\"*\"]`)             |\n| `disabled`          | Ignore all inbound DMs                                          |\n\n| Group policy          | Behavior                                               |\n| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n| `allowlist` (default) | Only groups matching the configured allowlist          |\n| `open`                | Bypass group allowlists (mention-gating still applies) |\n| `disabled`            | Block all group/room messages                          |\n\n<Note>\n`channels.defaults.groupPolicy` sets the default when a provider's `groupPolicy` is unset.\nPairing codes expire after 1 hour. Pending DM pairing requests are capped at **3 per channel**.\nIf a provider block is missing entirely (`channels.<provider>` absent), runtime group policy falls back to `allowlist` (fail-closed) with a startup warning.\n</Note>\n\n### Channel model overrides\n\nUse `channels.modelByChannel` to pin specific channel IDs to a model. Values accept `provider/model` or configured model aliases. The channel mapping applies when a session does not already have a model override (for example, set via `/model`).\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    modelByChannel: {\n      discord: {\n        \"123456789012345678\": \"anthropic/claude-opus-4-6\",\n      },\n      slack: {\n        C1234567890: \"openai/gpt-4.1\",\n      },\n      telegram: {\n        \"-1001234567890\": \"openai/gpt-4.1-mini\",\n        \"-1001234567890:topic:99\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### Channel defaults and heartbeat\n\nUse `channels.defaults` for shared group-policy and heartbeat behavior across providers:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    defaults: {\n      groupPolicy: \"allowlist\", // open | allowlist | disabled\n      heartbeat: {\n        showOk: false,\n        showAlerts: true,\n        useIndicator: true,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- `channels.defaults.groupPolicy`: fallback group policy when a provider-level `groupPolicy` is unset.\n- `channels.defaults.heartbeat.showOk`: include healthy channel statuses in heartbeat output.\n- `channels.defaults.heartbeat.showAlerts`: include degraded/error statuses in heartbeat output.\n- `channels.defaults.heartbeat.useIndicator`: render compact indicator-style heartbeat output.\n\n### WhatsApp\n\nWhatsApp runs through the gateway's web channel (Baileys Web). It starts automatically when a linked session exists.\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      dmPolicy: \"pairing\", // pairing | allowlist | open | disabled\n      allowFrom: [\"+15555550123\", \"+447700900123\"],\n      textChunkLimit: 4000,\n      chunkMode: \"length\", // length | newline\n      mediaMaxMb: 50,\n      sendReadReceipts: true, // blue ticks (false in self-chat mode)\n      groups: {\n        \"*\": { requireMention: true },\n      },\n      groupPolicy: \"allowlist\",\n      groupAllowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n    },\n  },\n  web: {\n    enabled: true,\n    heartbeatSeconds: 60,\n    reconnect: {\n      initialMs: 2000,\n      maxMs: 120000,\n      factor: 1.4,\n      jitter: 0.2,\n      maxAttempts: 0,\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n<Accordion title=\"Multi-account WhatsApp\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      accounts: {\n        default: {},\n        personal: {},\n        biz: {\n          // authDir: \"~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/biz\",\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- Outbound commands default to account `default` if present; otherwise the first configured account id (sorted).\n- Optional `channels.whatsapp.defaultAccount` overrides that fallback default account selection when it matches a configured account id.\n- Legacy single-account Baileys auth dir is migrated by `openclaw doctor` into `whatsapp/default`.\n- Per-account overrides: `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.sendReadReceipts`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.dmPolicy`, `channels.whatsapp.accounts.<id>.allowFrom`.\n\n</Accordion>\n\n[2851 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774011494490}}
{"type":"message","id":"c03499e4","parentId":"230525cf","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:17.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我搜索更多关于 tools.agentToAgent 配置的详细内容。","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_QkgFt4JE38h2pejAxFNxi2Cf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 30 \"### \\`tools.agentToAgent\\`\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":1379,"output":59,"cacheRead":50432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774011494492}}
{"type":"message","id":"75e9ab75","parentId":"c03499e4","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:17.939Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_QkgFt4JE38h2pejAxFNxi2Cf","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"API Key: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\nAuth Token: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nNotes:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":25,"aggregated":"API Key: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\nAuth Token: sk-kimi-Y311pdLbY8kXigdqhyjfKBjhNdzl4WRzJFderDmHC8eLPhwJMrTmSuG5e8jeaqND\n### `tools.agentToAgent`\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `tools.sessions`\n\nControls which sessions can be targeted by the session tools (`sessions_list`, `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`).\n\nDefault: `tree` (current session + sessions spawned by it, such as subagents).\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nNotes:","cwd":"/home/hochoy/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774011497937}}
{"type":"message","id":"29e564eb","parentId":"75e9ab75","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:21.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"现在我有了足够的信息。让我读取更多关于 session tools 的内容。","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_Oso3HeB16iHEhKBTcBEjPKeq","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/session-tool.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":402,"output":43,"cacheRead":51712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52157,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774011497940}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd3d02da","parentId":"29e564eb","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:58:21.209Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_Oso3HeB16iHEhKBTcBEjPKeq","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Agent session tools for listing sessions, fetching history, and sending cross-session messages\"\nread_when:\n  - Adding or modifying session tools\ntitle: \"Session Tools\"\n---\n\n# Session Tools\n\nGoal: small, hard-to-misuse tool set so agents can list sessions, fetch history, and send to another session.\n\n## Tool Names\n\n- `sessions_list`\n- `sessions_history`\n- `sessions_send`\n- `sessions_spawn`\n\n## Key Model\n\n- Main direct chat bucket is always the literal key `\"main\"` (resolved to the current agent’s main key).\n- Group chats use `agent:<agentId>:<channel>:group:<id>` or `agent:<agentId>:<channel>:channel:<id>` (pass the full key).\n- Cron jobs use `cron:<job.id>`.\n- Hooks use `hook:<uuid>` unless explicitly set.\n- Node sessions use `node-<nodeId>` unless explicitly set.\n\n`global` and `unknown` are reserved values and are never listed. If `session.scope = \"global\"`, we alias it to `main` for all tools so callers never see `global`.\n\n## sessions_list\n\nList sessions as an array of rows.\n\nParameters:\n\n- `kinds?: string[]` filter: any of `\"main\" | \"group\" | \"cron\" | \"hook\" | \"node\" | \"other\"`\n- `limit?: number` max rows (default: server default, clamp e.g. 200)\n- `activeMinutes?: number` only sessions updated within N minutes\n- `messageLimit?: number` 0 = no messages (default 0); >0 = include last N messages\n\nBehavior:\n\n- `messageLimit > 0` fetches `chat.history` per session and includes the last N messages.\n- Tool results are filtered out in list output; use `sessions_history` for tool messages.\n- When running in a **sandboxed** agent session, session tools default to **spawned-only visibility** (see below).\n\nRow shape (JSON):\n\n- `key`: session key (string)\n- `kind`: `main | group | cron | hook | node | other`\n- `channel`: `whatsapp | telegram | discord | signal | imessage | webchat | internal | unknown`\n- `displayName` (group display label if available)\n- `updatedAt` (ms)\n- `sessionId`\n- `model`, `contextTokens`, `totalTokens`\n- `thinkingLevel`, `verboseLevel`, `systemSent`, `abortedLastRun`\n- `sendPolicy` (session override if set)\n- `lastChannel`, `lastTo`\n- `deliveryContext` (normalized `{ channel, to, accountId }` when available)\n- `transcriptPath` (best-effort path derived from store dir + sessionId)\n- `messages?` (only when `messageLimit > 0`)\n\n## sessions_history\n\nFetch transcript for one session.\n\nParameters:\n\n- `sessionKey` (required; accepts session key or `sessionId` from `sessions_list`)\n- `limit?: number` max messages (server clamps)\n- `includeTools?: boolean` (default false)\n\nBehavior:\n\n- `includeTools=false` filters `role: \"toolResult\"` messages.\n- Returns messages array in the raw transcript format.\n- When given a `sessionId`, OpenClaw resolves it to the corresponding session key (missing ids error).\n\n## sessions_send\n\nSend a message into another session.\n\nParameters:\n\n- `sessionKey` (required; accepts session key or `sessionId` from `sessions_list`)\n- `message` (required)\n- `timeoutSeconds?: number` (default >0; 0 = fire-and-forget)\n\nBehavior:\n\n- `timeoutSeconds = 0`: enqueue and return `{ runId, status: \"accepted\" }`.\n- `timeoutSeconds > 0`: wait up to N seconds for completion, then return `{ runId, status: \"ok\", reply }`.\n- If wait times out: `{ runId, status: \"timeout\", error }`. Run continues; call `sessions_history` later.\n- If the run fails: `{ runId, status: \"error\", error }`.\n- Announce delivery runs after the primary run completes and is best-effort; `status: \"ok\"` does not guarantee the announce was delivered.\n- Waits via gateway `agent.wait` (server-side) so reconnects don't drop the wait.\n- Agent-to-agent message context is injected for the primary run.\n- Inter-session messages are persisted with `message.provenance.kind = \"inter_session\"` so transcript readers can distinguish routed agent instructions from external user input.\n- After the primary run completes, OpenClaw runs a **reply-back loop**:\n  - Round 2+ alternates between requester and target agents.\n  - Reply exactly `REPLY_SKIP` to stop the ping‑pong.\n  - Max turns is `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns` (0–5, default 5).\n- Once the loop ends, OpenClaw runs the **agent‑to‑agent announce step** (target agent only):\n  - Reply exactly `ANNOUNCE_SKIP` to stay silent.\n  - Any other reply is sent to the target channel.\n  - Announce step includes the original request + round‑1 reply + latest ping‑pong reply.\n\n## Channel Field\n\n- For groups, `channel` is the channel recorded on the session entry.\n- For direct chats, `channel` maps from `lastChannel`.\n- For cron/hook/node, `channel` is `internal`.\n- If missing, `channel` is `unknown`.\n\n## Security / Send Policy\n\nPolicy-based blocking by channel/chat type (not per session id).\n\n```json\n{\n  \"session\": {\n    \"sendPolicy\": {\n      \"rules\": [\n        {\n          \"match\": { \"channel\": \"discord\", \"chatType\": \"group\" },\n          \"action\": \"deny\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"default\": \"allow\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nRuntime override (per session entry):\n\n- `sendPolicy: \"allow\" | \"deny\"` (unset = inherit config)\n- Settable via `sessions.patch` or owner-only `/send on|off|inherit` (standalone message).\n\nEnforcement points:\n\n- `chat.send` / `agent` (gateway)\n- auto-reply delivery logic\n\n## sessions_spawn\n\nSpawn a sub-agent run in an isolated session and announce the result back to the requester chat channel.\n\nParameters:\n\n- `task` (required)\n- `label?` (optional; used for logs/UI)\n- `agentId?` (optional; spawn under another agent id if allowed)\n- `model?` (optional; overrides the sub-agent model; invalid values error)\n- `thinking?` (optional; overrides thinking level for the sub-agent run)\n- `runTimeoutSeconds?` (defaults to `agents.defaults.subagents.runTimeoutSeconds` when set, otherwise `0`; when set, aborts the sub-agent run after N seconds)\n- `thread?` (default false; request thread-bound routing for this spawn when supported by the channel/plugin)\n- `mode?` (`run|session`; defaults to `run`, but defaults to `session` when `thread=true`; `mode=\"session\"` requires `thread=true`)\n- `cleanup?` (`delete|keep`, default `keep`)\n- `sandbox?` (`inherit|require`, default `inherit`; `require` rejects spawn unless the target child runtime is sandboxed)\n- `attachments?` (optional array of inline files; subagent runtime only, ACP rejects). Each entry: `{ name, content, encoding?: \"utf8\" | \"base64\", mimeType? }`. Files are materialized into the child workspace at `.openclaw/attachments/<uuid>/`. Returns a receipt with sha256 per file.\n- `attachAs?` (optional; `{ mountPath? }` hint reserved for future mount implementations)\n\nAllowlist:\n\n- `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`: list of agent ids allowed via `agentId` (`[\"*\"]` to allow any). Default: only the requester agent.\n- Sandbox inheritance guard: if the requester session is sandboxed, `sessions_spawn` rejects targets that would run unsandboxed.\n\nDiscovery:\n\n- Use `agents_list` to discover which agent ids are allowed for `sessions_spawn`.\n\nBehavior:\n\n- Starts a new `agent:<agentId>:subagent:<uuid>` session with `deliver: false`.\n- Sub-agents default to the full tool set **minus session tools** (configurable via `tools.subagents.tools`).\n- Sub-agents are not allowed to call `sessions_spawn` (no sub-agent → sub-agent spawning).\n- Always non-blocking: returns `{ status: \"accepted\", runId, childSessionKey }` immediately.\n- With `thread=true`, channel plugins can bind delivery/routing to a thread target (Discord support is controlled by `session.threadBindings.*` and `channels.discord.threadBindings.*`).\n- After completion, OpenClaw runs a sub-agent **announce step** and posts the result to the requester chat channel.\n  - If the assistant final reply is empty, the latest `toolResult` from sub-agent history is included as `Result`.\n- Reply exactly `ANNOUNCE_SKIP` during the announce step to stay silent.\n- Announce replies are normalized to `Status`/`Result`/`Notes`; `Status` comes from runtime outcome (not model text).\n- Sub-agent sessions are auto-archived after `agents.defaults.subagents.archiveAfterMinutes` (default: 60).\n- Announce replies include a stats line (runtime, tokens, sessionKey/sessionId, transcript path, and optional cost).\n\n## Sandbox Session Visibility\n\nSession tools can be scoped to reduce cross-session access.\n\nDefault behavior:\n\n- `tools.sessions.visibility` defaults to `tree` (current session + spawned subagent sessions).\n- For sandboxed sessions, `agents.defaults.sandbox.sessionToolsVisibility` can hard-clamp visibility.\n\nConfig:\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      // default: \"tree\"\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      sandbox: {\n        // default: \"spawned\"\n        sessionToolsVisibility: \"spawned\", // or \"all\"\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nNotes:\n\n- `self`: only the current session key.\n- `tree`: current session + sessions spawned by the current session.\n- `agent`: any session belonging to the current agent id.\n- `all`: any session (cross-agent access still requires `tools.agentToAgent`).\n- When a session is sandboxed and `sessionToolsVisibility=\"spawned\"`, OpenClaw clamps visibility to `tree` even if you set `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774011501207}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca78ce3c","parentId":"dd3d02da","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:59:28.411Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"现在我有足够的权威文档内容了。让我为用户整理一份详细的 agent-to-agent 配置指南。","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"根据 OpenClaw 官方文档，以下是 **Agent-to-Agent 配置的权威详解**：\n\n---\n\n## 一、Agent-to-Agent 的两种模式\n\n| 模式 | 用途 | 配置位置 |\n|------|------|----------|\n| **Sub-agents** (子 Agent) | 后台并行任务，完成后汇报结果 | `agents.defaults.subagents` |\n| **Cross-agent messaging** (跨 Agent 消息) | 直接向其他 Agent 发送消息 | `tools.agentToAgent` + `sessions_send` |\n\n---\n\n## 二、Sub-agents 配置（官方文档 `/tools/subagents.md`）\n\n### 1. 基础配置\n\n```json5\n// ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      subagents: {\n        maxSpawnDepth: 2,        // 嵌套层级: 1=默认(平级), 2=可再spawn子agent\n        maxConcurrent: 8,        // 全局并发上限 (默认8)\n        maxChildrenPerAgent: 5,  // 每个agent最多同时运行子任务数 (默认5)\n        runTimeoutSeconds: 900,  // 默认超时秒数 (0=无超时)\n        model: \"kimi-coding/k2p5\", // 子agent默认模型\n        thinking: \"low\",         // 子agent默认思考级别\n        archiveAfterMinutes: 60, // 自动归档时间\n      },\n    },\n    list: [\n      {\n        id: \"main\",\n        subagents: {\n          allowAgents: [\"demo\", \"wechat-assistant\"]  // main可启动的agent白名单\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        id: \"demo\",\n        subagents: {\n          allowAgents: [\"wechat-assistant\"]  // demo可调用wechat-assistant\n        }\n      }\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### 2. 调用方式（`sessions_spawn` 工具）\n\n```javascript\nsessions_spawn({\n  task: \"帮我写一篇公众号文章\",\n  agentId: \"demo\",           // 可选，指定目标agent（需在allowAgents中）\n  label: \"article-task-1\",   // 可选标签，用于后续引用\n  mode: \"run\",               // \"run\"=一次性任务, \"session\"=持久会话\n  thread: false,             // true=绑定到Discord线程\n  timeoutSeconds: 600,\n  model: \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5\",  // 覆盖默认模型\n})\n```\n\n### 3. 嵌套层级说明（官方表格）\n\n| Depth | Session Key | 角色 | 能否继续spawn |\n|-------|-------------|------|---------------|\n| 0 | `agent:<id>:main` | 主 Agent | 永远可以 |\n| 1 | `agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>` | 子 Agent | 仅当 `maxSpawnDepth >= 2` |\n| 2 | `agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>:subagent:<uuid>` | 孙 Agent | 永远不可以 |\n\n### 4. 子 Agent 的工具权限\n\n- **默认**：子 Agent 获得**除 session 工具外的所有工具**\n- **当 `maxSpawnDepth >= 2`**：Depth-1 的 orchestrator 子 Agent 额外获得 `sessions_spawn`, `subagents`, `sessions_list`, `sessions_history`\n\n### 5. 子 Agent 工具限制配置\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    subagents: {\n      tools: {\n        deny: [\"gateway\", \"cron\"],  // 禁止的工具\n        // allow: [\"read\", \"exec\"]  // 如设置allow，则变为白名单模式\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 三、跨 Agent 消息配置（`tools.agentToAgent`）\n\n### 1. 启用配置（官方文档 `/gateway/configuration-reference.md`）\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: false,           // 默认关闭，必须显式启用\n      allow: [\"home\", \"work\"],  // 允许通信的agent白名单，[\"*\"]=允许所有\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### 2. 调用方式（`sessions_send` 工具）\n\n```javascript\n// 方式1: 通过 sessionKey 发送\nsessions_send({\n  sessionKey: \"agent:demo:feishu:direct:ou_xxx\",\n  message: \"文章写好了吗？\",\n  timeoutSeconds: 30  // 0= fire-and-forget, >0=等待回复\n})\n\n// 方式2: 通过 label 发送（之前spawn时设置的label）\nsessions_send({\n  label: \"article-task-1\",\n  message: \"进度如何？\"\n})\n```\n\n### 3. Ping-Pong 往返机制\n\n- 发送消息后，目标 Agent 回复，可继续往返对话\n- 最大往返轮数：`session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns`（0-5，默认5）\n- 回复 `REPLY_SKIP` 可停止往返\n\n---\n\n## 四、Session 工具可见性配置\n\n控制哪些 session 可被 `sessions_list` / `sessions_history` / `sessions_send` 访问：\n\n```json5\n{\n  tools: {\n    sessions: {\n      // \"self\" | \"tree\" | \"agent\" | \"all\"\n      // self=仅自己, tree=自己+子agent, agent=同agent所有session, all=所有session\n      visibility: \"tree\",\n    },\n  },\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      sandbox: {\n        sessionToolsVisibility: \"spawned\", // sandbox模式下强制限制为\"tree\"\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 五、Multi-Agent Routing 配置（官方文档 `/concepts/multi-agent.md`）\n\n### 完整示例：3个Agent + 飞书渠道路由\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace\",\n      model: \"kimi-coding/k2p5\",\n      subagents: {\n        maxSpawnDepth: 2,\n        maxConcurrent: 8,\n      },\n    },\n    list: [\n      {\n        id: \"main\",\n        default: true,  // 默认agent\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace\",\n        agentDir: \"~/.openclaw/agents/main/agent\",\n        subagents: {\n          allowAgents: [\"demo\", \"wechat-assistant\"]\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        id: \"demo\",\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-demo\",\n        agentDir: \"~/.openclaw/agents/demo/agent\",\n        subagents: {\n          allowAgents: [\"wechat-assistant\"]\n        },\n        tools: {\n          allow: [\"read\", \"exec\", \"write\", \"sessions_spawn\", \"sessions_send\"],\n          deny: [\"browser\", \"cron\"]\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        id: \"wechat-assistant\",\n        workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace-wechat-assistant\",\n        agentDir: \"~/.openclaw/agents/wechat-assistant/agent\",\n        sandbox: {\n          mode: \"all\",     // 该agent始终在sandbox中运行\n          scope: \"agent\",\n        }\n      }\n    ],\n  },\n\n  // 路由绑定：哪个渠道/账号的消息发给哪个agent\n  bindings: [\n    {\n      agentId: \"main\",\n      match: { \n        channel: \"feishu\", \n        accountId: \"main\"  // 飞书main账号的私聊\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      agentId: \"demo\",\n      match: { \n        channel: \"feishu\", \n        accountId: \"demo\",\n        peer: { kind: \"group\", id: \"oc_xxx\" }  // 特定群组\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      agentId: \"wechat-assistant\",\n      match: { \n        channel: \"feishu\", \n        accountId: \"wechat-assistant\" \n      }\n    }\n  ],\n\n  // 启用agent间通信\n  tools: {\n    agentToAgent: {\n      enabled: true,\n      allow: [\"main\", \"demo\", \"wechat-assistant\"],\n    },\n    sessions: {\n      visibility: \"tree\",  // 默认可见范围\n    },\n  },\n\n  channels: {\n    feishu: {\n      enabled: true,\n      dmPolicy: \"pairing\",\n      accounts: {\n        main: { appId: \"cli_xxx\", appSecret: \"xxx\" },\n        demo: { appId: \"cli_yyy\", appSecret: \"yyy\" },\n        \"wechat-assistant\": { appId: \"cli_zzz\", appSecret: \"zzz\" },\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 六、关键要点总结\n\n| 配置项 | 默认值 | 说明 |\n|--------|--------|------|\n| `agents.defaults.subagents.maxSpawnDepth` | `1` | 1=子agent不能再spawn，2=支持orchestrator模式 |\n| `agents.defaults.subagents.maxConcurrent` | `8` | 全局子agent并发上限 |\n| `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents` | `[self]` | 该agent可以spawn的agent白名单 |\n| `tools.agentToAgent.enabled` | `false` | 必须显式设为true才能跨agent通信 |\n| `tools.agentToAgent.allow` | `[]` | 允许通信的agent列表，`[\"*\"]`=全部 |\n| `tools.sessions.visibility` | `\"tree\"` | session工具可见范围 |\n| `session.agentToAgent.maxPingPongTurns` | `5` | 消息往返最大轮数 |\n\n**文档来源：**\n- `/tools/subagents.md` - 子agent完整配置\n- `/gateway/configuration-reference.md` - 配置字段参考\n- `/concepts/multi-agent.md` - 多agent路由\n- `/concepts/session-tool.md` - session工具使用"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":2469,"output":2150,"cacheRead":51968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774011501210}}
